1
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:22,940
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:24,350 --> 00:00:28,320
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:30,980 --> 00:00:36,070
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:37,270 --> 00:00:42,180
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:43,710 --> 00:00:46,990
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:50,060
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:50,770 --> 00:00:55,720
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:59,940
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:00:59,940 --> 00:01:03,220
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:03,760 --> 00:01:08,890
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:09,660 --> 00:01:12,920
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:16,280
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:16,690 --> 00:01:22,360
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:22,770 --> 00:01:26,020
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:29,350
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:33,790
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:33,790 --> 00:01:35,040
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,135 --> 00:01:37,760
=Episode 42=

19
00:01:42,085 --> 00:01:46,005
They say at this age,
we don't have to spell everything out.

20
00:01:47,126 --> 00:01:49,645
We just get each other and get by.

21
00:01:51,966 --> 00:01:55,246
We've understood each other
for half a lifetime.

22
00:01:56,126 --> 00:01:59,326
But that doesn't mean
we settle for everything.

23
00:02:00,365 --> 00:02:01,005
No.

24
00:02:02,246 --> 00:02:05,565
Today, I've got to speak my mind to you.

25
00:02:05,565 --> 00:02:06,326
Well,

26
00:02:06,806 --> 00:02:07,485
the two of us

27
00:02:09,005 --> 00:02:10,165
should get married.

28
00:02:11,366 --> 00:02:14,005
Yeah, I'll marry you.

29
00:02:15,045 --> 00:02:16,486
And you'll come live with me.

30
00:02:18,126 --> 00:02:19,325
Proper and formal.

31
00:02:27,246 --> 00:02:28,126
Say something.

32
00:02:29,045 --> 00:02:31,165
Too shy to speak?

33
00:02:34,325 --> 00:02:36,126
Here's some advice.

34
00:02:36,885 --> 00:02:37,445
Alright?

35
00:02:38,005 --> 00:02:40,526
You can't afford to be picky

36
00:02:40,526 --> 00:02:41,885
at your age.

37
00:02:41,885 --> 00:02:43,725
You don't have many options.

38
00:02:44,246 --> 00:02:44,800
Right?

39
00:02:45,406 --> 00:02:47,366
If you miss your chance with me...

40
00:02:47,366 --> 00:02:48,325
You know.

41
00:02:48,926 --> 00:02:49,725
Think about it.

42
00:02:50,445 --> 00:02:54,045
You won't get another chance like this.

43
00:02:56,325 --> 00:02:58,165
Weigh this carefully.

44
00:03:07,646 --> 00:03:08,565
What's wrong?

45
00:03:10,806 --> 00:03:12,605
Too much booze. Head's all fuzzy.

46
00:03:13,165 --> 00:03:14,005
Want me to hold you?

47
00:03:16,486 --> 00:03:17,086
Yeah.

48
00:03:25,005 --> 00:03:26,086
How is this a proposal?

49
00:03:30,325 --> 00:03:31,646
I have a ring.

50
00:03:32,725 --> 00:03:33,246
Here.

51
00:03:33,565 --> 00:03:34,686
I bought it ages ago.

52
00:03:34,686 --> 00:03:35,526
Qin'e helped me...

53
00:03:36,126 --> 00:03:37,646
Qin'e helped me pick it.

54
00:03:38,806 --> 00:03:41,045
Then the kid got sick,
so I never got the chance.

55
00:03:41,605 --> 00:03:43,445
If you say yes,

56
00:03:43,445 --> 00:03:46,445
we'll get the marriage certificate
in Ningzhou next week.

57
00:03:48,406 --> 00:03:49,526
Proper and formal.

58
00:03:50,686 --> 00:03:51,552
No messing around.

59
00:04:05,445 --> 00:04:06,486
What is this?

60
00:04:07,486 --> 00:04:09,045
It's Liu Yi's longevity lock.

61
00:04:09,765 --> 00:04:10,765
I'll exchange it.

62
00:04:15,486 --> 00:04:16,325
I will marry you.

63
00:04:23,885 --> 00:04:24,486
Come over.

64
00:04:33,606 --> 00:04:34,885
You need to live a long life.

65
00:04:36,246 --> 00:04:37,046
So we can

66
00:04:38,126 --> 00:04:39,366
keep tangling with each other.

67
00:04:41,965 --> 00:04:43,525
It's heavier than the ring.

68
00:04:49,686 --> 00:04:50,205
Go home.

69
00:05:00,565 --> 00:05:01,726
So lame.

70
00:05:20,126 --> 00:05:21,806
Why did I come here?

71
00:05:23,445 --> 00:05:24,126
Hua.

72
00:05:25,846 --> 00:05:26,445
Hua.

73
00:05:26,846 --> 00:05:27,686
Let me stay.

74
00:05:29,405 --> 00:05:29,965
Get lost.

75
00:06:31,392 --> 00:06:33,920
How long does it take to get
a pass to Hong Kong & Macau, China?

76
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,286
I'm not sure.

77
00:06:35,286 --> 00:06:36,525
You need to ask them.

78
00:06:37,445 --> 00:06:39,445
Get this form stamped
at the Youth League Office.

79
00:06:50,846 --> 00:06:51,445
Qin'e.

80
00:06:52,205 --> 00:06:52,806
Qin'e.

81
00:07:14,806 --> 00:07:16,606
Driving a taxi
doesn't require much skill.

82
00:07:17,126 --> 00:07:18,126
(Drive safe. Follow traffic rules.)
Just remember.

83
00:07:18,126 --> 00:07:20,645
Get more jobs. Drive faster.

84
00:07:21,445 --> 00:07:22,885
You know the roads in Chang'an?

85
00:07:22,885 --> 00:07:23,584
Yeah.

86
00:07:23,806 --> 00:07:25,645
There's no turning back once you start.

87
00:07:25,645 --> 00:07:28,445
You have to make 2000 a month
just to cover your lease.

88
00:07:29,286 --> 00:07:31,246
Once you get the car,
you drive every day.

89
00:07:31,565 --> 00:07:32,686
Follow the rules.

90
00:07:33,046 --> 00:07:36,126
If you get a complaint, you'll be fined.

91
00:07:36,352 --> 00:07:37,126
That won't happen.

92
00:07:37,366 --> 00:07:39,046
I'm driving to make money.

93
00:07:39,445 --> 00:07:40,405
Rest assured.

94
00:07:40,405 --> 00:07:42,126
Work hard, and you'll surely make money.

95
00:08:00,606 --> 00:08:02,005
Awesome.

96
00:08:04,965 --> 00:08:06,885
Here we go. Chopsticks.

97
00:08:09,726 --> 00:08:11,005
So elegant.

98
00:08:28,686 --> 00:08:29,246
Qin'e.

99
00:08:30,126 --> 00:08:31,205
I'm sorry.

100
00:08:41,925 --> 00:08:42,525
Qin'e.

101
00:08:43,966 --> 00:08:44,685
I'm sorry.

102
00:08:45,645 --> 00:08:46,726
I was talking nonsense.

103
00:08:47,525 --> 00:08:48,126
Forgive me.

104
00:08:48,805 --> 00:08:51,206
Don't worry, we'll work it out.

105
00:08:51,805 --> 00:08:52,566
This won't do.

106
00:08:52,966 --> 00:08:54,566
You look good.

107
00:08:55,885 --> 00:08:56,805
What are you doing?

108
00:08:57,326 --> 00:08:58,086
Idiot.

109
00:09:08,765 --> 00:09:09,366
Qin'e.

110
00:09:10,446 --> 00:09:11,525
I found a new job,

111
00:09:12,326 --> 00:09:13,005
driving a taxi.

112
00:09:13,765 --> 00:09:15,246
Base pay is 500 a month.

113
00:09:15,645 --> 00:09:17,566
There's a commission on every fare.

114
00:09:19,685 --> 00:09:21,045
As long as I get more jobs,

115
00:09:21,486 --> 00:09:22,685
I can save up money.

116
00:09:24,326 --> 00:09:24,925
Trust me.

117
00:09:26,112 --> 00:09:27,446
We'll cure the kid.

118
00:09:40,832 --> 00:09:42,606
We can cure our son.

119
00:09:47,925 --> 00:09:48,966
Yes, we can.

120
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:29,241
Master Chen.

121
00:10:30,441 --> 00:10:32,361
Has Qin'e been back since the morning?

122
00:10:33,001 --> 00:10:34,841
She came back and then left again.

123
00:10:37,160 --> 00:10:38,081
Let me use the phone.

124
00:10:48,721 --> 00:10:50,481
(This is the Diaojia Village Clinic.)

125
00:10:50,481 --> 00:10:51,441
(The National Forum)

126
00:10:51,441 --> 00:10:54,800
(on Pediatric Congenital Heart Disease
is being held in Guangzhou.)

127
00:10:55,961 --> 00:10:56,560
Hello.

128
00:11:03,560 --> 00:11:04,361
(Dozens of)

129
00:11:04,361 --> 00:11:07,121
(the country's
top pediatric cardiology experts)

130
00:11:07,121 --> 00:11:08,961
(are attending the meeting.)

131
00:11:09,961 --> 00:11:12,241
(This forum marks new progress)

132
00:11:12,241 --> 00:11:15,481
(in our country's achievements
in the treatment)

133
00:11:15,481 --> 00:11:17,361
(of children's
congenital heart disease.)

134
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:19,961
Hurry up.

135
00:11:20,841 --> 00:11:21,560
To Shanxi.

136
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:23,880
Faster, please.

137
00:11:24,841 --> 00:11:25,760
Why the rush?

138
00:11:26,081 --> 00:11:27,680
Just hurry.

139
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:28,560
How much is it?

140
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:29,201
Six yuan.

141
00:11:30,920 --> 00:11:31,800
8:40 PM.

142
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:34,160
Excuse me.

143
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:35,920
Any tickets to Guangzhou?

144
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:37,241
Nothing in the next three days.

145
00:11:37,241 --> 00:11:38,400
Come on, I want a ticket.

146
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:40,241
Anywhere near Guangzhou?

147
00:11:40,241 --> 00:11:42,721
Check the schedule and come back later.

148
00:11:43,081 --> 00:11:43,601
Go.

149
00:11:43,601 --> 00:11:44,560
- Next.
- No.

150
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,241
Wait a minute.

151
00:11:46,601 --> 00:11:48,280
Madam, here's the thing.

152
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:48,961
Could you check

153
00:11:48,961 --> 00:11:50,160
for any stations nearby?

154
00:11:50,160 --> 00:11:50,721
Any station.

155
00:11:50,721 --> 00:11:52,160
Southbound. Anywhere is fine.

156
00:11:52,160 --> 00:11:52,880
Okay?

157
00:11:52,880 --> 00:11:54,160
Just the earliest train.

158
00:11:59,989 --> 00:12:05,984
(First National Forum
on Pediatric Congenital Heart Disease)

159
00:12:14,321 --> 00:12:15,601
We must stick to the rules

160
00:12:16,001 --> 00:12:17,361
and the spirit of the meeting.

161
00:12:20,920 --> 00:12:21,560
Understand?

162
00:12:22,361 --> 00:12:23,081
Okay.

163
00:12:23,920 --> 00:12:24,601
Like this...

164
00:12:24,601 --> 00:12:25,880
Are you Dr. Zhang Haiqiang?

165
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:26,496
Me?

166
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:27,400
Yes.

167
00:12:29,361 --> 00:12:31,201
- You...
- Please save my child.

168
00:12:31,201 --> 00:12:32,400
What are you doing?

169
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:33,520
Why are you kneeling?

170
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:34,640
Please help us.

171
00:12:34,640 --> 00:12:35,920
Please stand up first.

172
00:12:35,920 --> 00:12:37,920
Stand up, and let's talk.

173
00:12:39,081 --> 00:12:40,481
Where are you from?

174
00:12:40,601 --> 00:12:41,680
I'm from Chang'an.

175
00:12:42,752 --> 00:12:43,640
How old is the child?

176
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:44,280
One year old.

177
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:45,441
One year old?

178
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:47,280
Can I take a look?

179
00:12:49,241 --> 00:12:50,640
You came at just the right time.

180
00:12:52,081 --> 00:12:54,481
The first surgery
for a similar case in China

181
00:12:54,961 --> 00:12:56,321
has been successful.

182
00:12:57,121 --> 00:12:58,241
But

183
00:12:59,201 --> 00:13:01,001
your child's condition

184
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:02,760
hasn't stabilized.

185
00:13:04,601 --> 00:13:05,920
Surgery carries risks.

186
00:13:06,721 --> 00:13:07,601
Let's wait for now.

187
00:13:08,201 --> 00:13:09,601
Let him grow a little more,

188
00:13:10,001 --> 00:13:11,560
and let the techniques develop.

189
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:13,721
So, there's still hope, right?

190
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:15,321
Be patient.

191
00:13:15,321 --> 00:13:17,800
Let your kid grow at his own pace,

192
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:18,920
normally.

193
00:13:19,361 --> 00:13:20,441
There will be hope.

194
00:13:20,880 --> 00:13:22,721
Complete the hospitalization procedures.

195
00:13:22,721 --> 00:13:24,441
Get your child a comprehensive check-up.

196
00:13:24,441 --> 00:13:26,121
Go home and feed him well.

197
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:28,721
That will help him grow.

198
00:13:29,800 --> 00:13:31,481
Let the baby have it for a while.

199
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:34,241
Is it fun?

200
00:13:37,961 --> 00:13:38,880
Sis.

201
00:13:39,201 --> 00:13:40,760
Could you watch him for me?

202
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:41,800
I'll buy him some food.

203
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:42,841
Okay, go ahead.

204
00:13:42,841 --> 00:13:43,601
Thank you.

205
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:50,520
Is it fun?

206
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:51,296
Not for eating.

207
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:54,121
Excuse me.

208
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:55,920
A congee, please.

209
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:56,640
Okay.

210
00:13:57,081 --> 00:13:57,760
How much?

211
00:13:58,040 --> 00:13:58,760
Fifty cents.

212
00:13:58,848 --> 00:13:59,481
Okay.

213
00:14:01,920 --> 00:14:02,624
Okay, thanks.

214
00:14:06,640 --> 00:14:07,961
Here's a bag for you.

215
00:14:13,961 --> 00:14:14,481
Pick three.

216
00:14:14,481 --> 00:14:15,008
Anything.

217
00:14:22,295 --> 00:14:25,504
(Inpatient)

218
00:15:11,001 --> 00:15:12,760
(Yi Qin'e decides to divorce.)

219
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:15,400
(She excels at playing roles on stage)

220
00:15:15,441 --> 00:15:17,721
(but struggles to live well off stage.)

221
00:15:18,601 --> 00:15:20,721
(All the unspoken affection)

222
00:15:21,560 --> 00:15:22,721
(becomes debts.)

223
00:15:23,760 --> 00:15:24,601
(Perhaps divorce)

224
00:15:24,841 --> 00:15:27,841
(is the last dignity
she could give Liu Hongbing.)

225
00:15:28,640 --> 00:15:29,481
(From now on,)

226
00:15:29,680 --> 00:15:31,640
(she will bear these debts alone.)

227
00:15:32,880 --> 00:15:36,680
(She chooses the single-plank bridge.
If it broke, that would be her fate.)

228
00:15:45,001 --> 00:15:46,201
Why's he sitting there?

229
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:48,441
What happened?

230
00:15:51,040 --> 00:15:52,841
Why did you have to get divorced?

231
00:15:52,961 --> 00:15:54,201
Just like that?

232
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:56,001
What were you doing?

233
00:15:57,441 --> 00:15:59,400
You pursued her so passionately.

234
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:00,081
And now?

235
00:16:00,321 --> 00:16:01,056
The kid is sick.

236
00:16:01,201 --> 00:16:02,481
And you're abandoning them?

237
00:16:03,121 --> 00:16:04,001
What are you thinking?

238
00:16:06,961 --> 00:16:07,721
Where's Laidi?

239
00:16:14,321 --> 00:16:15,321
What are you thinking?

240
00:16:23,800 --> 00:16:24,961
So you got divorced.

241
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:28,081
It's no big deal.

242
00:16:29,201 --> 00:16:29,880
Don't cry.

243
00:16:32,201 --> 00:16:34,481
Should I not have gotten married

244
00:16:35,601 --> 00:16:37,201
and had this baby?

245
00:16:39,160 --> 00:16:41,361
Don't speak like that.

246
00:16:42,721 --> 00:16:44,680
Don't dwell on the past. Look ahead.

247
00:16:46,081 --> 00:16:47,601
Focus on your opera singing.

248
00:16:47,601 --> 00:16:50,081
Leave the kid to your uncle and me.

249
00:16:50,441 --> 00:16:52,121
Three adults can't handle one kid?

250
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:55,800
None of the doctors we've seen
can cure him.

251
00:16:58,280 --> 00:17:00,081
I can't just watch him...

252
00:17:03,400 --> 00:17:05,080
He is my child.

253
00:17:09,721 --> 00:17:10,481
Stop crying.

254
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,360
I know you're suffering.

255
00:17:15,120 --> 00:17:15,760
But

256
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:19,921
you must take care of yourself
for the sake of your child.

257
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:22,441
Well,

258
00:17:23,840 --> 00:17:25,681
life can be tough, but we'll get by.

259
00:17:27,881 --> 00:17:29,401
Can my kid pull through this?

260
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:32,721
We can't submit to fate.

261
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:34,681
We have to believe in ourselves.

262
00:17:37,201 --> 00:17:37,800
Don't cry.

263
00:17:47,401 --> 00:17:47,921
Stop crying.

264
00:17:50,600 --> 00:17:51,201
We'll be fine.

265
00:17:56,360 --> 00:17:58,520
Why didn't you tell us
about the divorce?

266
00:17:58,520 --> 00:18:00,161
It's not something you do on a whim.

267
00:18:00,641 --> 00:18:02,001
She wouldn't let you tell us?

268
00:18:02,560 --> 00:18:04,961
She wouldn't let you pursue her,
but you did anyway.

269
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:05,961
I didn't know

270
00:18:06,560 --> 00:18:08,600
what she might do
if I didn't divorce her.

271
00:18:09,080 --> 00:18:11,721
She's a woman with a baby.
What can she possibly do?

272
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:14,120
You know what she's like.

273
00:18:14,641 --> 00:18:16,800
When she's determined,
no one can change her mind.

274
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:17,881
What can I do?

275
00:18:17,881 --> 00:18:19,241
Save your excuses.

276
00:18:20,481 --> 00:18:23,280
I liked you back then
for your persistence.

277
00:18:24,120 --> 00:18:26,800
But now, you're abandoning
your wife and child.

278
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:28,681
I'm not abandoning them, Uncle.

279
00:18:28,681 --> 00:18:29,481
Don't call me Uncle.

280
00:18:29,481 --> 00:18:30,840
You already divorced her.

281
00:18:31,721 --> 00:18:32,800
I have to...

282
00:18:34,441 --> 00:18:35,560
I have to cure the kid.

283
00:18:37,840 --> 00:18:40,201
I found a new job, driving a taxi.

284
00:18:40,721 --> 00:18:42,241
But I'll still be at their service.

285
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:43,961
I won't be living here.

286
00:18:44,201 --> 00:18:45,840
But everything else will be the same.

287
00:18:46,840 --> 00:18:48,241
You're both saving the kid.

288
00:18:49,401 --> 00:18:50,961
Why can't you live together?

289
00:18:51,881 --> 00:18:52,800
Why must you divorce?

290
00:18:53,201 --> 00:18:54,401
It's for the kid.

291
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:57,401
She won't have to
worry about me anymore.

292
00:18:58,961 --> 00:19:00,360
If she tells me

293
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:01,921
that she's taking the kid somewhere,

294
00:19:01,921 --> 00:19:03,360
I'll be here watching them.

295
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:04,881
I-I'll be right here...

296
00:19:12,961 --> 00:19:14,681
I don't understand you people.

297
00:19:27,800 --> 00:19:29,320
(From that day on,)

298
00:19:29,921 --> 00:19:31,520
(Yi Qin'e and Liu Hongbing)

299
00:19:31,721 --> 00:19:35,600
(Late 1990s)
(focused on making money to cure the kid.)

300
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:37,760
(Driving a taxi was hard,)

301
00:19:38,441 --> 00:19:40,280
(but it brought in some money.)

302
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:42,641
(Liu Hongbing scrimped)

303
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:45,681
(and saved every penny he earned.)

304
00:19:46,921 --> 00:19:50,600
(Though opera singing
wasn't as popular as before,)

305
00:19:51,881 --> 00:19:54,721
(as long as there were elders,
someone would hire the troupe.)

306
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:57,001
(When going to perform,)

307
00:19:57,280 --> 00:19:59,921
(Yi Qin'e had to bring Liu Yi along.)

308
00:20:00,721 --> 00:20:03,721
(Life and the stage
became increasingly inseparable.)

309
00:20:04,441 --> 00:20:06,241
(She also began to adapt.)

310
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:08,600
(Finally, one day,)

311
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:11,560
(Yi Qin'e returned here.)

312
00:20:12,481 --> 00:20:14,120
(To Xiangyang Commune.)

313
00:20:16,600 --> 00:20:17,120
Laidi.

314
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:19,721
Say hi to Mom.

315
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:21,681
Let Mommy hold you, okay?

316
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:26,441
Look at this stage.

317
00:20:27,120 --> 00:20:29,840
It's where your mom first made her name.

318
00:20:29,921 --> 00:20:31,040
Where she started.

319
00:20:31,481 --> 00:20:32,401
Give me a hand.

320
00:20:32,401 --> 00:20:33,800
Watch your step.

321
00:20:33,961 --> 00:20:35,080
No real blades.

322
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:46,840
Isn't your mom amazing?

323
00:20:47,921 --> 00:20:49,241
She's playing the general.

324
00:20:49,560 --> 00:20:52,560
These people are all afraid of her
and listen to her.

325
00:20:55,441 --> 00:20:56,441
Bravo!

326
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:57,401
Bravo!

327
00:21:01,201 --> 00:21:01,840
Bravo!

328
00:21:06,881 --> 00:21:07,881
Bravo!

329
00:21:07,881 --> 00:21:09,161
That's my daughter.

330
00:21:14,441 --> 00:21:15,161
Bravo!

331
00:21:15,641 --> 00:21:16,560
Bravo!

332
00:21:22,800 --> 00:21:23,360
Sis.

333
00:21:24,001 --> 00:21:25,721
I've sprayed Qin'e's costume.

334
00:21:26,001 --> 00:21:27,080
- Thanks.
- No problem.

335
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:28,921
- Anyone else's need spraying?
- No.

336
00:21:28,921 --> 00:21:29,600
That's it.

337
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:31,201
- Let me know if you need anything.
- Okay.

338
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,360
Liu Yi.

339
00:21:43,401 --> 00:21:44,881
See who I am.

340
00:21:46,001 --> 00:21:47,001
See who I am.

341
00:21:49,481 --> 00:21:50,320
Are you hungry?

342
00:21:51,401 --> 00:21:52,881
Mommy will pour you some water.

343
00:21:53,360 --> 00:21:53,984
Da.

344
00:21:58,560 --> 00:21:59,721
You can say "Dad" now?

345
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:05,961
Dad bought it for you?

346
00:22:06,441 --> 00:22:07,360
You can say "Dad" now?

347
00:22:07,961 --> 00:22:08,840
Say it again.

348
00:22:09,560 --> 00:22:10,401
Da...

349
00:22:10,401 --> 00:22:11,201
Da...

350
00:22:11,201 --> 00:22:11,721
Da...

351
00:22:12,080 --> 00:22:12,921
Say "Dad".

352
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:17,001
Da, da, da.

353
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:19,840
Dad.

354
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:23,161
Say "Mom".

355
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:24,800
Say "Mom".

356
00:22:27,961 --> 00:22:28,800
Mom.

357
00:22:34,600 --> 00:22:35,320
Get some rest.

358
00:22:35,560 --> 00:22:36,096
Come on.

359
00:22:36,481 --> 00:22:37,241
You must be tired.

360
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:40,320
Your uncle bought this for you.
Have it when it's warm.

361
00:22:40,921 --> 00:22:42,721
Don't worry about me, Aunt Hua.

362
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:45,120
How can I not worry?

363
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:49,520
Don't be sad.

364
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:53,001
Didn't the doctor say?

365
00:22:53,001 --> 00:22:56,080
The kid's just a little slow to develop.

366
00:22:56,441 --> 00:22:59,201
Might be later than other kids.

367
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:00,481
No rush.

368
00:23:03,001 --> 00:23:04,320
He's grown this big.

369
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:07,161
You two have had it tough.

370
00:23:07,681 --> 00:23:08,681
It will get better.

371
00:23:16,280 --> 00:23:16,961
Yeah.

372
00:23:16,961 --> 00:23:18,120
One more thing.

373
00:23:18,600 --> 00:23:19,641
My nephew

374
00:23:19,641 --> 00:23:21,161
is studying computers at school.

375
00:23:21,641 --> 00:23:22,721
He told me

376
00:23:22,721 --> 00:23:25,681
that many people
will do business online.

377
00:23:26,360 --> 00:23:28,280
I find this quite new.

378
00:23:29,280 --> 00:23:30,600
I want to learn about it.

379
00:23:31,881 --> 00:23:33,560
Do you know anyone

380
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:34,881
to get me a computer?

381
00:23:37,161 --> 00:23:37,721
Alright.

382
00:23:37,721 --> 00:23:39,560
Call me back if you find someone.

383
00:23:40,001 --> 00:23:41,080
Okay, ask around for me.

384
00:23:45,481 --> 00:23:46,080
Buddy.

385
00:23:46,441 --> 00:23:47,961
A bitter gourd? That's fancy.

386
00:23:53,721 --> 00:23:55,201
- Want a bite?
- No, thanks.

387
00:23:55,760 --> 00:23:56,721
Keep it for yourself.

388
00:23:56,721 --> 00:23:58,001
My life is plenty sweet.

389
00:24:04,360 --> 00:24:06,641
Stop eating. Will you help us?

390
00:24:07,080 --> 00:24:08,760
Have you ever seen a boss work?

391
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:10,401
Don't be cocky.

392
00:24:10,401 --> 00:24:12,800
You're a boss?
You're still wet behind the ears.

393
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:13,641
- I'll be the boss...
- Seriously.

394
00:24:13,641 --> 00:24:14,681
sooner or later.

395
00:24:14,681 --> 00:24:16,161
You're just so special.

396
00:24:16,161 --> 00:24:17,120
Everyone's working.

397
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:18,921
Only you're idling about
in that stupid hat.

398
00:24:18,921 --> 00:24:20,401
Exactly, no manners.

399
00:24:20,401 --> 00:24:22,641
Dachui is a mutt acting like a wolf.

400
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:24,320
You people...

401
00:24:24,320 --> 00:24:25,401
He's putting on airs.

402
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:27,760
What are you doing?

403
00:24:30,481 --> 00:24:31,921
How did you just pop up?

404
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:33,600
You scared me.

405
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:36,800
Everyone took some.
Why are you picking on me?

406
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:38,201
Still, you shouldn't.

407
00:24:38,201 --> 00:24:40,001
You're the Troupe Leader's mom.

408
00:24:40,481 --> 00:24:41,320
Set an example.

409
00:24:42,800 --> 00:24:44,280
So high and mighty.

410
00:24:44,280 --> 00:24:45,760
You think I'm money-obsessed?

411
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:47,401
Back when I was in Jiuyangou,

412
00:24:47,401 --> 00:24:48,721
I never took a thing from others

413
00:24:49,280 --> 00:24:51,280
no matter how poor we were.

414
00:24:51,280 --> 00:24:52,040
Alright.

415
00:24:52,401 --> 00:24:54,961
I'm taking these back for Liu Yi.

416
00:24:55,520 --> 00:24:56,201
Think about it.

417
00:24:57,520 --> 00:25:00,320
Laidi is working herself to death,

418
00:25:01,641 --> 00:25:04,520
saving money for the child's surgery.

419
00:25:05,001 --> 00:25:07,120
She's been singing day and night.

420
00:25:07,560 --> 00:25:09,040
She takes after you.

421
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:11,120
So high and mighty.

422
00:25:12,001 --> 00:25:12,800
What a fool.

423
00:25:13,560 --> 00:25:15,241
Suffering just to save face.

424
00:25:16,120 --> 00:25:17,001
Tell me.

425
00:25:17,001 --> 00:25:19,241
Why did she have to get divorced?

426
00:25:19,241 --> 00:25:20,280
So determined.

427
00:25:20,760 --> 00:25:21,600
Now what?

428
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:25,001
Liu Hongbing is living it up
while she suffers here.

429
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:26,241
Stop rambling here.

430
00:25:26,241 --> 00:25:27,681
Bring the kid. It's time to eat.

431
00:25:29,241 --> 00:25:30,560
Why is my daughter

432
00:25:32,001 --> 00:25:33,360
suffering like this?

433
00:25:40,241 --> 00:25:41,161
Seriously.

434
00:25:41,161 --> 00:25:42,921
The rich get richer,
and the poor poorer.

435
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:44,800
We're working ourselves to death

436
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:46,001
just to make

437
00:25:46,001 --> 00:25:46,921
some petty money.

438
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:49,360
Some people go to those fancy teahouses

439
00:25:49,360 --> 00:25:50,120
and sit on laps,

440
00:25:50,120 --> 00:25:51,641
sweet-talking someone over wine.

441
00:25:52,201 --> 00:25:55,201
Singing opera doesn't matter anymore.

442
00:25:55,201 --> 00:25:56,040
I have big thighs.

443
00:25:56,040 --> 00:25:57,441
So sit on my lap. Come on.

444
00:25:57,441 --> 00:25:58,320
What nonsense.

445
00:25:59,120 --> 00:26:00,520
- Seriously.
- Enjoy.

446
00:26:01,401 --> 00:26:02,201
Uncle Sanyuan.

447
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:04,401
Do you know about that teahouse?

448
00:26:04,721 --> 00:26:07,001
I heard they get paid 10,000

449
00:26:07,001 --> 00:26:09,120
or even up to 100,000 for one show.

450
00:26:09,681 --> 00:26:11,040
Great deal. You should go.

451
00:26:11,481 --> 00:26:12,600
I'm not good enough.

452
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:15,001
They disgrace the profession.

453
00:26:15,001 --> 00:26:16,681
They have no self-respect.

454
00:26:17,280 --> 00:26:18,481
No one will respect them.

455
00:26:18,481 --> 00:26:20,040
Dignity can't fill your stomach.

456
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:22,280
Auntie, you played Yang Paifeng, right?

457
00:26:22,641 --> 00:26:23,681
Yes, I'm Yi Qin'e.

458
00:26:23,681 --> 00:26:24,360
What's your name?

459
00:26:24,360 --> 00:26:25,241
I'm Song Yu.

460
00:26:25,241 --> 00:26:27,921
Daughter of the head cook.
The fire-tending girl.

461
00:26:27,921 --> 00:26:29,641
I think I could be Yang Paifeng too.

462
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:31,481
You tend the fire?

463
00:26:32,120 --> 00:26:33,280
I used to do the same.

464
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:34,040
Really?

465
00:26:35,760 --> 00:26:36,360
Little girl.

466
00:26:36,681 --> 00:26:38,120
Come here, let me talk to you.

467
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:41,641
Yang Paifeng can fight. Can you fight?

468
00:26:41,641 --> 00:26:43,001
Of course.

469
00:26:43,001 --> 00:26:44,120
That's not enough.

470
00:26:44,120 --> 00:26:45,520
You have to take beatings too.

471
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:46,201
Can you?

472
00:26:46,560 --> 00:26:47,800
My dad hits me every day.

473
00:26:50,441 --> 00:26:51,800
What a strong alkaline taste.

474
00:26:52,721 --> 00:26:55,360
It tastes just like the Mo
of our County Troupe.

475
00:26:58,921 --> 00:26:59,968
What's your name again?

476
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:00,881
Song Yu.

477
00:27:01,921 --> 00:27:03,232
Your dad's also surnamed Song?

478
00:27:03,881 --> 00:27:05,481
Do you hear yourself?

479
00:27:05,481 --> 00:27:07,201
What else could his last name be?

480
00:27:07,201 --> 00:27:07,921
Hu, like yours?

481
00:27:08,881 --> 00:27:10,280
Get your dad here.

482
00:27:11,040 --> 00:27:11,681
Dad.

483
00:27:12,241 --> 00:27:13,241
What is that for?

484
00:27:13,681 --> 00:27:15,921
The Mo reminds me of Master Song
from the County Troupe.

485
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:17,721
I want to see if it's him.

486
00:27:27,961 --> 00:27:28,641
Master Song.

487
00:27:33,881 --> 00:27:34,481
Master Song.

488
00:27:34,481 --> 00:27:35,320
Sanyuan.

489
00:27:35,881 --> 00:27:37,001
It really is you.

490
00:27:37,001 --> 00:27:38,120
Master Song.

491
00:27:38,120 --> 00:27:39,681
I knew you were coming.

492
00:27:40,320 --> 00:27:41,481
Seriously?

493
00:27:41,481 --> 00:27:42,401
You knew we were here

494
00:27:42,401 --> 00:27:43,881
and didn't come out to say hi?

495
00:27:43,881 --> 00:27:44,881
Why were you hiding?

496
00:27:45,441 --> 00:27:46,201
Caixiang.

497
00:27:47,961 --> 00:27:48,961
Master Song.

498
00:27:49,600 --> 00:27:50,401
Laidi.

499
00:27:51,120 --> 00:27:52,721
You've become a big star.

500
00:27:52,721 --> 00:27:54,320
Excellent.

501
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:13,080
Sir.

502
00:28:13,921 --> 00:28:14,641
One Mo, please.

503
00:28:14,944 --> 00:28:15,721
Alright.

504
00:28:16,961 --> 00:28:18,441
Put some dried tofu and egg.

505
00:28:18,441 --> 00:28:19,800
And shredded potato.

506
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:21,800
Forget it. Skip the egg.

507
00:28:22,001 --> 00:28:22,921
Add extra dried tofu.

508
00:28:23,120 --> 00:28:23,641
Alright.

509
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:26,688
How much?

510
00:28:27,001 --> 00:28:27,641
Fifty cents.

511
00:28:29,921 --> 00:28:30,600
Here.

512
00:28:30,881 --> 00:28:31,392
Okay.

513
00:28:32,320 --> 00:28:33,800
Young man, your Mo is ready.

514
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:38,040
Sir.

515
00:28:40,600 --> 00:28:41,201
Thanks.

516
00:28:41,201 --> 00:28:41,721
No problem.

517
00:28:57,681 --> 00:28:58,360
Sir.

518
00:28:59,681 --> 00:29:00,681
Where's the dried tofu?

519
00:29:00,681 --> 00:29:01,881
At the bottom.

520
00:29:13,201 --> 00:29:14,600
I want this one.

521
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:15,760
Okay.

522
00:29:15,760 --> 00:29:17,120
Nirvana and the Eagles.

523
00:29:17,760 --> 00:29:19,161
Here's your five yuan change.

524
00:29:19,161 --> 00:29:20,080
Thanks, handsome.

525
00:29:20,441 --> 00:29:21,001
Thanks.

526
00:29:21,001 --> 00:29:22,080
Take a look at this one.

527
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:23,681
Take a look. Handsome, want one?

528
00:29:24,080 --> 00:29:25,080
Okay.

529
00:29:25,080 --> 00:29:26,710
Here, ten yuan change.

530
00:29:26,710 --> 00:29:27,721
Look at these two.

531
00:29:27,721 --> 00:29:28,921
Got the latest ones too.

532
00:29:30,760 --> 00:29:31,424
Have a look.

533
00:29:31,681 --> 00:29:32,641
What bands do you like?

534
00:29:35,441 --> 00:29:36,001
Linkin Park.

535
00:29:36,001 --> 00:29:36,641
No?

536
00:29:36,641 --> 00:29:37,441
Okay, thanks.

537
00:29:37,721 --> 00:29:38,560
- Come on.
- Young man.

538
00:29:38,816 --> 00:29:40,201
Who said you could set up here?

539
00:29:41,681 --> 00:29:42,441
What's wrong?

540
00:29:42,441 --> 00:29:43,120
"What's wrong?"

541
00:29:43,441 --> 00:29:44,961
You're blocking my business.

542
00:29:44,961 --> 00:29:46,080
Don't you know the rules?

543
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:47,401
What do you mean?

544
00:29:48,241 --> 00:29:48,921
Take a look.

545
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:51,280
I own that audio shop over there.

546
00:29:51,280 --> 00:29:54,080
How am I supposed to do business
if you sell tapes here?

547
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:56,001
You sell pirated copies too?

548
00:29:56,800 --> 00:29:58,320
No, I sell the real thing.

549
00:29:58,600 --> 00:29:59,600
I sell pirated copies.

550
00:29:59,600 --> 00:30:00,560
We'll just keep out of

551
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:01,881
each other's business.

552
00:30:02,721 --> 00:30:03,360
Get lost.

553
00:30:03,800 --> 00:30:04,704
Go somewhere else.

554
00:30:05,001 --> 00:30:06,401
No way. I'm selling right here.

555
00:30:07,560 --> 00:30:08,280
Young man.

556
00:30:08,721 --> 00:30:09,560
You're tough, huh?

557
00:30:14,001 --> 00:30:15,040
Come and take a look.

558
00:30:15,961 --> 00:30:16,560
Come on.

559
00:30:17,320 --> 00:30:18,120
Two discs.

560
00:30:18,881 --> 00:30:19,961
Come to me for more.

561
00:30:19,961 --> 00:30:20,921
I'll be right here.

562
00:30:22,881 --> 00:30:23,520
Just up ahead.

563
00:30:23,840 --> 00:30:24,800
Right there.

564
00:30:26,881 --> 00:30:27,481
That's him.

565
00:30:27,481 --> 00:30:28,360
Blue jacket.

566
00:30:28,881 --> 00:30:29,401
Stop.

567
00:30:31,520 --> 00:30:32,161
Don't run.

568
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:38,600
Brat.

569
00:30:38,600 --> 00:30:39,320
What's going on?

570
00:30:39,600 --> 00:30:40,360
Don't run.

571
00:30:43,721 --> 00:30:44,560
Excuse me.

572
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:45,641
Police.

573
00:30:45,641 --> 00:30:46,441
Coming through.

574
00:30:46,441 --> 00:30:47,401
We're after him.

575
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:49,401
It's urgent.

576
00:30:49,401 --> 00:30:50,040
Don't run.

577
00:31:00,320 --> 00:31:01,760
What are you

578
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:03,320
cheering for?

579
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:04,401
Huh?

580
00:31:04,401 --> 00:31:05,040
Not the head.

581
00:31:05,280 --> 00:31:06,080
Don't hit my head.

582
00:31:06,080 --> 00:31:08,961
Skipping classes wasn't enough?
You've started this?

583
00:31:09,921 --> 00:31:11,040
Why was I running

584
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:11,681
with you?

585
00:31:11,681 --> 00:31:12,881
It made me an accomplice.

586
00:31:13,560 --> 00:31:14,112
Come on.

587
00:31:14,961 --> 00:31:15,648
Turn yourself in.

588
00:31:16,001 --> 00:31:17,241
For what?

589
00:31:17,241 --> 00:31:18,881
I'm selling cut-out tapes.

590
00:31:19,280 --> 00:31:19,921
They chased you

591
00:31:19,921 --> 00:31:21,080
because of some tapes?

592
00:31:21,721 --> 00:31:23,280
Those hicks have no clue.

593
00:31:23,760 --> 00:31:25,921
This is heavy metal rock music
from abroad.

594
00:31:26,320 --> 00:31:28,120
They thought I was selling scrap metal.

595
00:31:28,881 --> 00:31:29,600
Stupid, huh?

596
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:32,201
Idiot.

597
00:31:34,161 --> 00:31:35,001
Still no.

598
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:38,320
We got you into that technical school.

599
00:31:38,320 --> 00:31:39,560
And you're skipping class,

600
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:40,800
selling "metal"?

601
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:43,760
I'm just trying to make money.

602
00:31:44,721 --> 00:31:45,921
What for?

603
00:31:46,520 --> 00:31:48,120
Just tell me if you want something.

604
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:49,280
Have we treated you badly?

605
00:31:50,280 --> 00:31:51,520
No, you haven't.

606
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:53,001
That's why I can't ask for money.

607
00:31:53,641 --> 00:31:56,161
I'm not like Gao Wufu,
who's draining you.

608
00:31:56,881 --> 00:31:57,881
Gao Wufu.

609
00:31:58,481 --> 00:31:59,080
Gao Wufu.

610
00:31:59,441 --> 00:32:00,241
Not on my head.

611
00:32:00,241 --> 00:32:01,481
Show some respect.

612
00:32:02,360 --> 00:32:03,360
You'll call me by my name

613
00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:04,760
once you graduate, huh?

614
00:32:05,280 --> 00:32:06,360
That's different.

615
00:32:06,560 --> 00:32:08,360
That guy shows up, asking you

616
00:32:08,360 --> 00:32:09,560
and my sister for money.

617
00:32:10,120 --> 00:32:11,080
I won't be like him.

618
00:32:13,120 --> 00:32:14,401
How many times have I told you?

619
00:32:15,040 --> 00:32:16,320
Don't worry about the money.

620
00:32:16,881 --> 00:32:18,241
Tell me if you need anything.

621
00:32:19,320 --> 00:32:22,320
Your sister has been exhausted lately.

622
00:32:23,001 --> 00:32:24,120
Give her some peace of mind.

623
00:32:26,520 --> 00:32:28,120
Stop messing with that junk metal.

624
00:32:32,001 --> 00:32:34,001
This is heavy metal.

625
00:32:38,326 --> 00:32:42,080
(Study Hard, Mao Zedong)

626
00:32:50,241 --> 00:32:51,600
Zhang Guangrong wrote to me,

627
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:53,320
asking me to go back.

628
00:32:54,320 --> 00:32:54,921
What's wrong?

629
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:57,481
He's going south for work.

630
00:32:59,161 --> 00:33:00,881
Zhang Hao
is taking the Gaokao this year.

631
00:33:00,881 --> 00:33:02,120
Someone should be home

632
00:33:02,401 --> 00:33:03,161
to look after him.

633
00:33:03,961 --> 00:33:05,241
I bought a ticket for tomorrow.

634
00:33:05,921 --> 00:33:06,481
Go ahead.

635
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:07,881
Look after the kid.

636
00:33:08,401 --> 00:33:09,401
And about Qin'e.

637
00:33:11,641 --> 00:33:13,161
Don't interfere too much.

638
00:33:14,161 --> 00:33:15,280
Don't meddle with it.

639
00:33:15,560 --> 00:33:17,360
If something really comes up,

640
00:33:17,360 --> 00:33:18,401
then lend a hand.

641
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:20,760
I'm her uncle. I know.

642
00:33:21,560 --> 00:33:24,520
I'm not afraid you'll do too little.
It's quite the opposite.

643
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:27,320
She's grown up. She can make decisions.

644
00:33:28,201 --> 00:33:28,961
And you.

645
00:33:29,961 --> 00:33:30,848
Don't push yourself.

646
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:34,641
Hongbing.

647
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:36,360
Have you been staying up late?

648
00:33:37,001 --> 00:33:38,360
You look even more worn out.

649
00:33:40,280 --> 00:33:41,360
Save your breath.

650
00:33:41,961 --> 00:33:43,721
Just worry me less. That's all I ask.

651
00:33:49,641 --> 00:33:50,401
Get off.

652
00:33:53,120 --> 00:33:53,800
What's wrong?

653
00:33:54,241 --> 00:33:54,881
Get going.

654
00:33:55,881 --> 00:33:58,040
Hongbing, how is Liu Yi?

655
00:34:00,481 --> 00:34:01,280
Same as always.

656
00:34:02,080 --> 00:34:03,080
Will he have surgery?

657
00:34:03,520 --> 00:34:06,641
My mom said
there's a cure for his illness now.

658
00:34:06,641 --> 00:34:07,201
Exactly.

659
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:09,281
The first surgery was successful.

660
00:34:09,281 --> 00:34:11,720
There's a bit of hope now.

661
00:34:12,560 --> 00:34:14,441
That's why I must work hard
to earn money.

662
00:34:15,904 --> 00:34:16,921
How much are you short?

663
00:34:19,961 --> 00:34:21,560
Why? Are you covering the gap?

664
00:34:23,401 --> 00:34:24,481
Mind your own business.

665
00:34:26,361 --> 00:34:28,200
Do you regret having the kid?

666
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:30,336
What do you mean?

667
00:34:36,001 --> 00:34:37,240
Have you ever thought

668
00:34:38,240 --> 00:34:39,160
that Liu Yi

669
00:34:42,001 --> 00:34:43,281
is destined to be like this?

670
00:34:45,321 --> 00:34:46,361
You little brat.

671
00:34:46,361 --> 00:34:48,120
Do you even hear yourself?

672
00:34:48,441 --> 00:34:51,481
Y-You're starting to speak for fate now?

673
00:34:51,481 --> 00:34:52,080
Aren't you?

674
00:34:52,080 --> 00:34:52,640
I'm off.

675
00:34:57,761 --> 00:34:58,680
Leave the metal.

676
00:34:59,361 --> 00:34:59,881
What?

677
00:35:00,640 --> 00:35:01,921
Leave the metal.

678
00:35:02,801 --> 00:35:03,801
Why?

679
00:35:03,801 --> 00:35:04,961
"Why?"

680
00:35:04,961 --> 00:35:06,481
Why does a student need those?

681
00:35:06,881 --> 00:35:08,281
Still thinking of selling them?

682
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:10,240
These are hard to come by.

683
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,321
I paid for them.

684
00:35:11,321 --> 00:35:13,001
Fine, I'm buying from you.

685
00:35:13,361 --> 00:35:13,921
Here.

686
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:16,600
Hongbing, listen to me.

687
00:35:16,600 --> 00:35:17,640
Not interested.

688
00:35:17,640 --> 00:35:18,720
This isn't about money.

689
00:35:18,720 --> 00:35:19,321
Hongbing.

690
00:35:19,321 --> 00:35:20,441
Just take it.

691
00:35:20,441 --> 00:35:21,401
- Stop nagging.
- Hongbing.

692
00:35:23,600 --> 00:35:24,416
It's not enough.

693
00:35:27,240 --> 00:35:27,881
It's not enough.

694
00:35:32,832 --> 00:35:33,841
(Diligence is the path
to the mountain of knowledge)

695
00:35:33,841 --> 00:35:36,001
Mr. Zhu, it's getting late.

696
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:37,841
Let me toast you
with tea instead of wine.

697
00:35:37,841 --> 00:35:38,680
No, no.

698
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:39,881
I should be toasting you.

699
00:35:39,881 --> 00:35:41,841
You're the Queen of Qinqiang opera.

700
00:35:42,200 --> 00:35:44,720
I can never get enough
of your performances.

701
00:35:45,921 --> 00:35:47,680
Stop toasting each other.

702
00:35:47,680 --> 00:35:49,001
It's getting late.

703
00:35:49,001 --> 00:35:50,761
Let's finish this last drink and go.

704
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:52,281
We have a show tomorrow.

705
00:35:52,281 --> 00:35:53,001
Yeah.

706
00:35:53,361 --> 00:35:54,841
Who do you think you are?

707
00:35:55,321 --> 00:35:58,240
I'm talking to the lead.
What's it to you?

708
00:35:58,240 --> 00:35:59,560
I'm the Northwest Drum King...

709
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:00,281
Enough.

710
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:01,240
Stop talking.

711
00:36:01,240 --> 00:36:02,080
Sorry, Mr. Zhu.

712
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:03,040
He's a bit drunk.

713
00:36:03,040 --> 00:36:03,560
Sorry.

714
00:36:03,560 --> 00:36:05,200
Mr. Zhu, you're too kind.

715
00:36:05,200 --> 00:36:07,720
Just call us
if you want to hear me sing.

716
00:36:07,720 --> 00:36:08,961
We'll come to sing for you.

717
00:36:08,961 --> 00:36:09,600
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

718
00:36:09,600 --> 00:36:11,001
- Serving the people.
- Anytime.

719
00:36:11,001 --> 00:36:12,080
Here's to you.

720
00:36:12,361 --> 00:36:12,960
Yeah.

721
00:36:14,016 --> 00:36:14,600
Alright.

722
00:36:15,961 --> 00:36:16,841
You know,

723
00:36:16,841 --> 00:36:17,520
this time,

724
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:20,240
I didn't see the fire breathing.

725
00:36:20,761 --> 00:36:21,921
- Not so perfect.
- I know.

726
00:36:21,984 --> 00:36:22,841
Mr. Zhu, take care.

727
00:36:22,841 --> 00:36:25,961
But "You Xi Hu" isn't suited
for a joyful occasion.

728
00:36:25,961 --> 00:36:27,881
Next time, host a cultural special.

729
00:36:27,881 --> 00:36:30,520
We'll showcase all the special skills
of Qinqiang opera.

730
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:31,441
- Yeah.
- Okay.

731
00:36:31,441 --> 00:36:33,281
- It's your contribution.
- Yeah.

732
00:36:33,281 --> 00:36:34,520
We're very grateful.

733
00:36:34,520 --> 00:36:36,560
Such bootlickers.

734
00:36:36,560 --> 00:36:37,921
Money doesn't make you special.

735
00:36:37,921 --> 00:36:39,120
- Take care, Mr. Zhu.
- Take care.

736
00:36:39,120 --> 00:36:39,720
Mr. Zhu.

737
00:36:47,040 --> 00:36:47,841
Sanyuan.

738
00:36:48,881 --> 00:36:51,481
Laidi looks like

739
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:54,281
she's been exhausted.

740
00:36:55,120 --> 00:36:56,401
Her child

741
00:36:57,200 --> 00:36:59,120
has a congenital disease.

742
00:36:59,441 --> 00:37:00,680
Heart problem.

743
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:03,881
Some developmental delays too.

744
00:37:04,441 --> 00:37:06,200
And she's running such a big troupe.

745
00:37:06,200 --> 00:37:07,040
That's why.

746
00:37:10,921 --> 00:37:13,520
She's such a good kid.
Why is it happening?

747
00:37:18,401 --> 00:37:19,264
What about your son?

748
00:37:19,680 --> 00:37:20,441
Has he come back?

749
00:37:21,240 --> 00:37:21,921
Yeah.

750
00:37:23,401 --> 00:37:25,801
He did well in the army after enlisting.

751
00:37:25,801 --> 00:37:27,701
He got a commendation and a promotion.

752
00:37:27,701 --> 00:37:28,961
He's settled there.

753
00:37:29,401 --> 00:37:30,560
A few years back,

754
00:37:31,120 --> 00:37:32,600
he said he'd bring me over.

755
00:37:32,801 --> 00:37:34,961
But you don't want to go anywhere
when you're old.

756
00:37:37,401 --> 00:37:39,361
Exactly. At our age, best not to travel.

757
00:37:39,361 --> 00:37:39,936
Yeah.

758
00:37:42,921 --> 00:37:44,361
Wait, you're not old at all.

759
00:37:47,720 --> 00:37:48,801
You have a young daughter.

760
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:50,761
You've still got it.

761
00:37:50,761 --> 00:37:52,200
What were you thinking?

762
00:37:52,720 --> 00:37:54,160
I adopted her.

763
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:56,720
I'm adopted.

764
00:37:56,720 --> 00:37:59,240
It was raining the day my dad found me.

765
00:37:59,240 --> 00:38:00,520
That's why I'm called Song Yu.

766
00:38:03,321 --> 00:38:04,001
Uncle.

767
00:38:04,001 --> 00:38:06,160
How were those moves I just did?

768
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:07,281
Can I play Yang Paifeng?

769
00:38:07,841 --> 00:38:08,761
Yes, you can.

770
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:11,881
But kiddo,

771
00:38:12,321 --> 00:38:14,200
this path is very tough.

772
00:38:14,481 --> 00:38:16,441
I want to learn from Aunt Qin'e.

773
00:38:16,864 --> 00:38:17,481
Alright.

774
00:38:18,160 --> 00:38:20,441
Have your dad bring you to Chang'an.

775
00:38:20,841 --> 00:38:22,761
Stay at Aunt Qin'e's house.

776
00:38:23,281 --> 00:38:24,961
I'll have her take you in.

777
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:27,080
Dad, let's go to Chang'an.

778
00:38:27,560 --> 00:38:28,361
Bring her.

779
00:38:28,361 --> 00:38:29,001
Okay.

780
00:38:29,921 --> 00:38:31,001
Check on the fire.

781
00:38:31,001 --> 00:38:32,120
The banquet will start soon.

782
00:38:33,961 --> 00:38:34,801
Take it easy.

783
00:38:41,361 --> 00:38:44,160
Things have changed so much
over the years.

784
00:38:44,520 --> 00:38:46,881
The County Troupe has little work.

785
00:38:47,881 --> 00:38:49,120
Everyone's on their own now.

786
00:38:50,281 --> 00:38:52,160
The young ladies
don't sing opera anymore.

787
00:38:52,160 --> 00:38:53,321
They sing pop songs.

788
00:38:53,961 --> 00:38:55,961
Or they get married and have kids.

789
00:38:56,680 --> 00:38:58,120
Men go back to the countryside.

790
00:38:58,560 --> 00:39:01,361
Machines farm the land now.
Not much use for them.

791
00:39:01,361 --> 00:39:02,881
So they go out to work.

792
00:39:03,401 --> 00:39:04,281
All sorts of jobs.

793
00:39:05,040 --> 00:39:06,481
Hardly anyone sings opera now.

794
00:39:07,321 --> 00:39:08,080
Same thing.

795
00:39:09,080 --> 00:39:13,240
You know how glorious
the factory workers were in the city.

796
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:14,560
Same thing.

797
00:39:17,680 --> 00:39:19,881
You know, Gu passed away.

798
00:39:20,441 --> 00:39:23,240
If he hadn't,
seeing opera decline like this

799
00:39:24,321 --> 00:39:25,881
would've broken his heart.

800
00:39:28,560 --> 00:39:30,761
It's fine. Life goes on.

801
00:39:34,401 --> 00:39:35,040
Dada...

802
00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:41,761
Dada...

803
00:39:42,441 --> 00:39:43,921
Watch him. Don't let him fall.

804
00:39:44,441 --> 00:39:45,040
Dada...

805
00:39:47,481 --> 00:39:48,520
Here, have some water.

806
00:39:49,481 --> 00:39:50,361
Tired?

807
00:39:50,921 --> 00:39:51,600
I'm used to it.

808
00:39:52,921 --> 00:39:56,801
I didn't expect Song Yu and Yi
to get along so well.

809
00:39:59,120 --> 00:40:01,761
You were about her age
when you first joined the troupe.

810
00:40:08,361 --> 00:40:09,720
You performed here, right?

811
00:40:10,240 --> 00:40:10,921
Yeah.

812
00:40:11,720 --> 00:40:12,600
Yang Paifeng.

813
00:40:13,441 --> 00:40:14,841
That was my first time on stage.

814
00:40:15,720 --> 00:40:18,921
So abrupt. I never imagined
so many people watching.

815
00:40:20,441 --> 00:40:22,120
Then this is your lucky place.

816
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:25,640
Maybe you'll have good news
about the kid when you go back.

817
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:32,761
Bang...

818
00:40:33,321 --> 00:40:34,160
Bang...

819
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:38,080
♪Waiting for dawn♪

820
00:40:39,281 --> 00:40:43,120
♪At midnight♪

821
00:40:44,441 --> 00:40:48,001
♪Longing for the spring breeze♪

822
00:40:49,481 --> 00:40:53,001
♪In winter♪

823
00:40:54,001 --> 00:40:58,001
♪Longing for the Red Army♪

824
00:40:58,801 --> 00:41:03,040
♪To come♪

825
00:41:03,801 --> 00:41:12,401
♪The hills are ablaze with azaleas♪

826
00:42:37,984 --> 00:42:41,888
(Liu Yi, March)

827
00:42:48,421 --> 00:42:56,384
♪The wind howls♪

828
00:42:58,768 --> 00:43:03,810
♪The mist is thick♪

829
00:43:05,209 --> 00:43:06,784
(Preview)

830
00:43:09,001 --> 00:43:10,881
Heavy metal from abroad.

831
00:43:11,001 --> 00:43:12,281
You want to watch movies too?

832
00:43:12,361 --> 00:43:14,801
No wonder nobody watches opera anymore.

833
00:43:15,200 --> 00:43:18,801
How come the cost is so much higher
than what you showed me last time?

834
00:43:18,801 --> 00:43:19,961
I know a gig organizer.

835
00:43:19,961 --> 00:43:21,200
He's got plenty of jobs.

836
00:43:21,361 --> 00:43:23,321
A beautiful song for everyone.

837
00:43:23,481 --> 00:43:25,080
Have some standards.

838
00:43:25,080 --> 00:43:26,961
You're ruining the craft, you know?

839
00:43:26,961 --> 00:43:28,680
I'm the deputy leader
of the Youth Troupe.

840
00:43:28,841 --> 00:43:31,560
I'm doing this not just for Liu Yi,
but for everyone.

841
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

842
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

843
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

844
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

845
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

846
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

847
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

848
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

849
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

850
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

851
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

852
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

853
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

854
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

855
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

856
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

857
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

858
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

859
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

860
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

861
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪

